<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-03-26T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-03-26T19:00:00-05:00" n="86" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d86">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00 R 294/148: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-03-26T19:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 26,
                                        1923—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>121. For Wadsworth. W–13. Your W–12, March 26.</p>
                        <p>The fixation of interest on deficits of the 12 annual installments at 4¼%
                            is suggested. This is the average rate here and is also the rate payable
                            on the three years’ arrears of interest on the debt of Great Britain. If
                            you should find it desirable, however, you may agree to a 4% interest
                            rate.</p>
                        <p>In reply to your W–14<note n="99" xml:id="d86fn99">Not printed.</note>
                            you should send any further suggestions that in your opinion should be
                            considered by this Government.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>